last_episode_to_air.name: The Last Word
last_episode_to_air.overview: Does war always have the last word? Jason wrestles with guilt and searches for closure in Afghanistan. The Decker investigation comes to a close, Ray starts his new chapter and the new-look BRAVO jumps right into the next mission.

name: SEAL Team
overview: Military drama following the professional and personal lives of the most elite unit of Navy SEALs as they train, plan and execute the most dangerous, high stakes missions our country can ask of them.

episodes.name: Tip of the Spear
episodes.overview: Team Bravo, an elite Tier One Navy SEAL unit, is sent on a clandestine mission to capture a most-wanted terrorist alive.  Meanwhile, team leader Jason Hayes must deal with personal issues affecting his marriage and family.

episodes.name: Other Lives
episodes.overview: While on an evidence-collecting mission in Syria, Jason and the SEAL Team find innocent civilians in desperate need of rescue just as enemy forces close in on them. Also, while on the mission, the team debates whether or not to tell Ray that his wife has gone into labor.

episodes.name: Boarding Party
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL team must rescue a group of researchers being held hostage on a ship in the South China Sea. Also, Clay is ranked in the “bottom five” of his class, jeopardizing his future as a SEAL

episodes.name: Ghosts of Christmas Future
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team refuse to abort a mission to capture a dangerous war criminal after it goes sideways. Also, Clay’s controversial father, Ash Spenser, comes to town on his book tour.

episodes.name: Collapse
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team must protect the American Embassy in South Sudan when the ambassador refuses to evacuate as the country becomes increasingly unstable. Also, Clay and Stella take their relationship to the next level.

episodes.name: The Spinning Wheel
episodes.overview: The SEAL Team must work with Jason’s longtime rival, Beau Fuller, and his team to plan and perfect a raid under the watchful eye of top military brass. Also, Clay delivers solemn news to a teammate’s next of kin.

episodes.name: Borderlines
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team must rescue an undercover CIA operative after she is captured by radical terrorists to be used as a bargaining chip. Also, Clay undergoes the final harrowing exercise for his candidacy into Tier One.

episodes.name: The Exchange
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team have mixed feelings when they are tasked with bringing home an American soldier who was captured after deserting, in exchange for detainees in Gitmo.

episodes.name: Rolling Dark
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL team must rescue a Russian scientist and his wife and bring them across the Afghanistan border to safety as Chinese and Russian Special Forces close in, intent on stopping them. Also, Clay endures his first day with Jason’s unit.

episodes.name: Pattern of Life
episodes.overview: Tensions are high when Jason and the SEAL Team enter a Yemeni house to locate a cell phone linked to a terrorist network, and interrogate the family while the daughter lays in critical condition after being accidentally shot.

episodes.name: Containment
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL team are sent to intercept the sale of nuclear weapons, but the mission goes sideways when they must make the treacherous journey back to base with nukes that have unsecured fuel rods. Also, Ray is sidelined with a shoulder injury, and Jason and Alana are shocked by their kids’ reactions when the topic of their reunion is brought up.

episodes.name: The Upside Down
episodes.overview: While on a mission to retrieve a downed top-secret drone, Jason and the SEAL Team disobey orders so they can save Clay, who is trapped beneath a room full of armed terrorists. Also, Clay and Stella’s relationship takes a new turn.

episodes.name: Getaway Day
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team must leave their families immediately when their deployment date is moved up after the team they were going to relieve is ambushed. Also, Jason and Alana make a big decision about their future, and Clay and Stella feel the weight of his marriage proposal.

episodes.name: Call Out
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team settle into deployment life and get closer to discovering who ambushed Echo Team after Mandy gets a lead from an unlikely source on the base.

episodes.name: No Man's Land
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team close in on avenging the deaths of Echo Team when they find the money that funded their murder on a nearby poppy farm that was previously used to make heroin. Also, Jason meets an intriguing woman on the base.

episodes.name: Never Get Out of the Boat
episodes.overview: Jason leads the SEAL Team on a dangerous daytime mission where Sonny is wounded and must now rely on Clay and his brothers to save his life.

episodes.name: In Name Only
episodes.overview: As Jason and the SEAL Team come closer to avenging the loss of Echo Team, Mandy takes matters into her own hands after her boss won’t green-light her mission to take out their biggest target. Also, Jason is unsure of where his relationship with Amy stands.

episodes.name: Credible Threat
episodes.overview: Jason and the SEAL Team are tasked with protecting a delegation of congressmen and department of defense officials who come to Jalalabad for a publicity tour even though a credible threat has been made against them.

episodes.name: Takedown
episodes.overview: The SEAL Team sends Ray undercover in a busy spice market to make a high-stakes money swap, and Jason attempts to take down a terrorist known to wear a suicide belt. Also, Ray realizes the devastating consequences of his decisions.

episodes.name: Enemy of My Enemy
episodes.overview: The lives of Jason and the SEAL Team are in jeopardy when a risky mission to capture a highly valuable target may actually be a trap. Also, Clay and Davis commiserate about the frustrations of having long distance relationships, and Ray has a meeting regarding his involvement with the accidental death of the local boy that could affect his military career.

episodes.name: The Graveyard of Empires
episodes.overview: Following a helicopter crash, the SEAL Team must proceed with the mission as hostiles bear down on them and an injured and impaired Jason goes after their target alone.

episodes.name: The Cost of Doing Business
episodes.overview: After Jason lies about his concussion to get cleared for combat, he and the SEAL Team plan a final mission to avenge Echo Team’s deaths once and for all before they return home from deployment.

episodes.name: Fracture
episodes.overview: Jason and Bravo Team head to the Gulf of Guinea to rescue American hostages after an oil platform is overtaken by armed militants.

episodes.name: Never Say Die
episodes.overview: Jason and Bravo Team travel to Saudi Arabia, where extremists take hold of an underground water source and threaten to release anthrax into the water supply. Also, Ray contemplates joining another team.

episodes.name: The Worst of Conditions
episodes.overview: After tragedy strikes, Jason is faced with a huge decision regarding his future with Bravo Team.

episodes.name: All That Matters
episodes.overview: Bravo Team is in Mumbai to rescue a U.S. Foreign Service officer being held hostage by radicals who attacked the city. Also, Jason reevaluates his parenting style and finds a way to connect with his kids.

episodes.name: Say Again Your Last
episodes.overview: While tasked with rescuing a group of American students held hostage in Mumbai, Bravo Team suffers life-threatening injuries.

episodes.name: Hold What You Got
episodes.overview: Bravo Team partners with the Mexican Marines to hunt the head of one of the most powerful and lethal drug cartels in Mexico.

episodes.name: Outside the Wire
episodes.overview: Bravo Team continues to follow tips that will lead to Andres Doza, the head of one of the most powerful and lethal drug cartels in Mexico.

episodes.name: Parallax
episodes.overview: Jason and Mandy go undercover as a couple on vacation at an upscale night club in Mexico City in order to track one of Andres Doza's cartel members.

episodes.name: Santa Muerte
episodes.overview: Following an ambush, the SEAL team suspects someone on the inside is leaking information to the cartel.

episodes.name: Prisoner's Dilemma
episodes.overview: The hunt for Andres Doza comes to a head when the SEAL Team makes one last ditch effort to find and capture the leader of one of the most powerful and lethal drug cartels in Mexico.

episodes.name: Backwards in High Heels
episodes.overview: Bravo Team partners with the British Special Air Service to rescue passengers on a hijacked plane who are taken hostage by terrorists.

episodes.name: Things Not Seen
episodes.overview: Bravo Team travels to Turkey to rescue a young American who voluntarily married an ISIS leader.

episodes.name: Time to Shine
episodes.overview: Bravo Team desperately works to save Sonny from a life-threatening situation, after he becomes trapped in a submarine torpedo tube during a clandestine mission off the coast of North Korea.

episodes.name: What Appears to Be
episodes.overview: Bravo Team works with the Congolese Army on a covert mission to capture the head of a rebel militia group. Jason argues with Emma about college. Sonny and Davis make a big decision about their future.

episodes.name: You Only Die Once
episodes.overview: Bravo Team sets out on a special ops mission to take down the financier and mastermind behind several terrorist attacks.

episodes.name: Dirt, Dirt, Gucci
episodes.overview: As Bravo Team prepares for what they expect to be a “cushy” deployment with the luxury of staying in a hotel in the Philippines, Jason tries to find a way to pay for Emma’s college.

episodes.name: Paradise Lost
episodes.overview: While Bravo Team is deployed to train Filipino SEALs, a surprise bomb attack in Manila leaves them in peril.

episodes.name: Payback
episodes.overview: Bravo Team is out for revenge as they search for the person responsible for the surprise bomb attack that left one of their own in peril.

episodes.name: Medicate and Isolate
episodes.overview: While Bravo Team is on a recovery mission in Mali, their friend, former Navy SEAL Brett Swan, continues to struggle with his mental health.

episodes.name: Rock Bottom
episodes.overview: The tension between Jason and Ray comes to a head, and Lisa faces her final test in officer candidate school.

episodes.name: My Life for Yours
episodes.overview: Bravo Team desperately searches for Ray after he gets separated from them while in enemy territory.

episodes.name: Never Out of the Fight
episodes.overview: Bravo team’s future is on the line when Commander Shaw recommends they be split up, but Jason’s unit has one final mission to prove him wrong.

episodes.name: Welcome to the Refuge
episodes.overview: Jason Hayes leads the team on a mission in Serbia to track down an organization linked to the bombing of multiple American military outposts.

episodes.name: Ignore and Override
episodes.overview: Bravo Team continues their mission in Serbia to track down an organization linked to the bombing of multiple American military outposts, when Jason Hayes’ past returns to haunt him and leaves him contemplating his future.

episodes.name: Theory and Methodology
episodes.overview: Bravo Team is on a mission in Azerbaijan to help retake a power plant in order to avoid political instability in the area.

episodes.name: The Strength of the Wolf
episodes.overview: Tensions boil over among Bravo members when they disagree while training for a mission, and Jason must select a new candidate to join the team.

episodes.name: All Along the Watchtower (1)
episodes.overview: Jason pleads to be sent to help Ray and Clay, who are abroad on a mission to protect a U.S. ambassador when their compound is attacked.

episodes.name: All Along the Watchtower (2)
episodes.overview: While on a mission abroad to protect U.S. ambassador Nicole Marsden, Bravo Team must fight off enemy attackers trying to infiltrate their compound.

episodes.name: The Ones You Can't See
episodes.overview: As Jason contemplates surgery for an injury, Bravo Team is on a mission abroad to help the secret service prevent a sniper attack on U.S. dignitaries.

episodes.name: Danger Crossing
episodes.overview: While Jason is sidelined with an injury, Ray takes over as Bravo 1 and leads the team on a mission to rescue a marine pilot who was shot down in enemy territory.

episodes.name: Kill or Cure
episodes.overview: Bravo team is on a mission to protect aid convoys in an Ebola hot zone after a warlord steals preserved samples of the virus that can be weaponized.

episodes.name: Unbecoming an Officer
episodes.overview: Jason leads Bravo Team on his first mission back following surgery, and Ensign Davis faces disciplinary action

episodes.name: Siege Protocol
episodes.overview: Amid several life-altering moments on the home front, Bravo Team travels overseas to extract a CIA agent who is being held hostage. As the situation escalates, the Tactical Operations Center is compromised and Bravo’s support team comes face-to-face with the enemy.

episodes.name: Fog of War
episodes.overview: Following a mission failure, Bravo Team conducts a high-stakes After Action Review to identify who’s responsible for a possible career-ending mistake.

episodes.name: Objects in Mirror
episodes.overview: Bravo Team travels overseas for a foreign training exercise to disguise their true mission – to rescue a high-value target that is being held hostage. Also, NASCAR driver Austin Dillon gives the team a special driving lesson.

episodes.name: Rules of Engagement
episodes.overview: While Bravo Team is on a special reconnaissance mission abroad, they are diverted to protect a group of American engineers and the dam they are constructing from a terrorist attack. The rules of engagement raise the level of danger, as the team is not permitted to use their weapons unless the enemy fires first.

episodes.name: Last Known Location
episodes.overview: Tensions flare on the home front, as Sonny faces disciplinary action, Clay considers a new career path and Jason faces pressure from Capt. Lindell to consider the next phase of his career, all while Bravo Team prepares for a three-month deployment in Afghanistan.

episodes.name: Drawdown
episodes.overview: As Bravo Team begins their deployment in Afghanistan during peace negotiations, Sonny reports to an Air Force base in Texas to serve his disciplinary training action, where he gets reacquainted with Hannah, a childhood friend.

episodes.name: Edge of Nowhere
episodes.overview: Bravo Team searches for a new terrorist group leader who is orchestrating violent resistance to peace negotiations in Afghanistan. Also, Clay learns what it means to be a leader and Sonny works to repair his relationship with his father in Texas.

episodes.name: In the Blind
episodes.overview: Bravo Team gets ambushed by enemy forces during a mission to extract a potential link to a new terrorist leader. Also, Sonny considers planting roots in his hometown.

episodes.name: No Choice in Duty
episodes.overview: While Jason escorts Mandy on a condolence visit to the family of a fallen informant, Ray leads Bravo on an urgent mission when they are confronted with a time-sensitive lead on a terrorist leader’s location. Also, Davis reveals to the team that the terrorist leader they’ve been searching for is related to a target from Jason’s past, and Sonny rejoins Bravo team in Afghanistan.

episodes.name: God of War
episodes.overview: Bravo Team enters enemy territory in the snowy Spin Ghar Mountain Range to capture Al-Hazred, the leader of a terrorist group and son of the terrorist leader that Jason took down early in his career and made him Bravo One. When they are attacked, Jason and Cerberus, Bravo's canine member, are separated from the team.

episodes.name: The New Normal
episodes.overview: Bravo Team struggles to adjust to a new team dynamic after several members make life-altering career decisions.

episodes.name: Shockwave
episodes.overview: When Warrant Officer Ray Perry goes missing following an explosion in Tunisia, his former teammates wrestle with how to help their brother and his family while Bravo Team is sidelined.

episodes.name: The Carrot or The Stick
episodes.overview: With no leads on Ray’s whereabouts, Jason pushes Bravo team to extreme lengths and considers crossing a dangerous line to help locate their missing brother. Meanwhile, Ray tries to survive captivity.

episodes.name: Horror Has a Face
episodes.overview: As Ensign Davis tracks Ray’s location to a shipping container in the Mediterranean Ocean, Bravo team becomes increasingly desperate to rescue their brother before it’s too late.

episodes.name: All In
episodes.overview: As Bravo continues grappling with major changes, the team spins up on a mission in Ecuador. Also, Natalie presents a life-changing idea to Jason.

episodes.name: Cover for Action
episodes.overview: When Jason returns to Bravo, tensions rise as Ray outranks him on a mission to recover military drones in Syria. Sonny receives surprising news from Texas.

episodes.name: Reckoning
episodes.overview: As Ray continues to lead the mission in Syria, the stakes grow higher when members of Bravo team learn the truth about their target.

episodes.name: A Question of Honor
episodes.overview: Jason’s career and freedom hang in the balance when Command accuses him of committing a horrific crime during a mission. With Bravo under a no-contact order, Jason must fight this battle without his brothers.

episodes.name: Limits of Loyalty
episodes.overview: Jason is put on trial with a potential career-ending outcome, without knowing if his closest friend, Ray, has his back. Also, Stella moves in with Clay, and Sonny visits Hannah to help her prepare for the arrival of their baby.

episodes.name: Rearview Mirror
episodes.overview: Jason's visit with a former teammate causes him to reevaluate his role as team leader. Also, several Bravo members grapple with their personal relationships when Command sends them on an unexpected mission to the coast of Africa.

episodes.name: Do No Harm
episodes.overview: Bravo is tasked with bringing a defecting Boko Haram lieutenant into U.S. custody, but the mission goes sideways when the target gets attacked. Sonny drops the ball as Bravo’s rep on the USS Keating, and the entire team pays the price.

episodes.name: Hollow at the Core
episodes.overview: Bravo is tasked with a covert mission to infiltrate a Boko Haram camp, hack its data network and rescue an American hostage.

episodes.name: Nightmare of My Choice
episodes.overview: Bravo joins forces to protect a crucial Nigerian pipeline under attack by Boko Haram. But when a team member is injured, Jason and Clay fight to save his life, and Bravo discovers an even more dangerous enemy is attacking them.

episodes.name: One Life To Live
episodes.overview: Bravo takes a devastating hit that will change the team forever, and forces each of the members to make some big personal decisions. Fourth season finale.

episodes.name: Trust, But Verify (1)
episodes.overview: Everyone on Bravo is shocked when they learn a training exercise is really cover for a covert mission to get a weapons expert out of one of the most dangerous countries in the world.

episodes.name: Trust, But Verify (2)
episodes.overview: When Bravo’s operation is compromised, they must figure out how to escape undetected from one of the most dangerous countries in the world.

episodes.name: Nine Ten
episodes.overview: As members of Bravo team travel to New York City, they reflect on a day that shaped each of their lives forever.

episodes.name: Need to Know (1)
episodes.overview: As each member of Bravo confronts major family obstacles, the team gets spun up on a sudden mission in Africa. When the intel alters their plan, the team finds themselves in a rush to prevent a major terrorist attack.

episodes.name: Frog On The Tracks (2)
episodes.overview: Team Bravo races against the clock to prevent a terrorist attack, while attempting to locate and capture their enemy. Preoccupied with questions, Jason must make a tough call to get the answers he so deeply craves.

episodes.name: Man on Fire (3)
episodes.overview: Bravo manages to escape their SUV engulfed in flames, but plans go awry when Jason's personal and professional lives become intertwined and he's forced to make decisions that put Bravo's jobs and lives at risk. The team works through disagreements, reveals exciting personal news and an unlikely hero emerges.

episodes.name: What's Past Is Prologue
episodes.overview: Bravo returns to Afghanistan to continue the fight against the Taliban, and the Team ruminates on America's longtime involvement in the War on Terror.

episodes.name: Conspicuous Gallantry
episodes.overview: After an op gone sideways lands the whole team in the hospital, Bravo must create a little chaos to stay calm, while Clay tries to piece together what went wrong.

episodes.name: Close to Home
episodes.overview: Jason seeks refuge at home while Ray leads Bravo Team on an op accompanying British forces.

episodes.name: Head On
episodes.overview: Bravo Team is presented with a mission in South America unlike any other, while tensions surrounding Jason’s leadership are at an all-time high.

episodes.name: Violence of Action
episodes.overview: Bravo Team is still on the ground in South America working against the Iranian nuclear project. Multiple high stakes missions only make the team’s interpersonal problems more obvious to all.

episodes.name: Keys To Heaven
episodes.overview: Jason must confront his deepest fears on the road to healing while Clay and Sonny are forced to take certain matters into their own hands.

episodes.name: Pillar Of Strength
episodes.overview: Bravo will need all hands on deck for a massive mission to shut down the Venezuelan nuclear program, but the biggest threat to their success could be one of their own.

episodes.name: All Bravo Stations
episodes.overview: Bravo must make a daring escape before they can put Venezuela in their rearview mirror, but they find themselves on even less stable ground when they return home to Virginia Beach.

episodes.name: Low-Impact
episodes.overview: BRAVO battles to survive a devastating ambush that will leave the team forever altered.

episodes.name: Crawl, Walk, Run
episodes.overview: BRAVO is deployed on a high-stakes mission in Russian controlled territory as Clay battles with his recovery.

episodes.name: Growing Pains
episodes.overview: BRAVO finds unlikely allies as they are deployed to Northern Syria to track down those responsible for the attack on the U.S.S. Crampton.

episodes.name: Phantom Pattern
episodes.overview: BRAVO works with the YPJ to suss out who is responsible for the bombing of the U.S.S. Crampton while struggling to accept their newest Team Member.

episodes.name: Thunderstruck
episodes.overview: A missed opportunity deepens the mistrust between Jason and Omar, and puts Bravo and their partner force in the crosshairs of a powerful enemy.

episodes.name: Watch Your 6
episodes.overview: Back home from Syria, Bravo unexpectedly finds themselves on a deeply personal mission.

episodes.name: Strange Bedfellows
episodes.overview: BRAVO is called back to Syria to handle some unfinished business.

episodes.name: Aces and Eights
episodes.overview: BRAVO heads to Amman, Jordan to find the Iranian General who has backed Yasiri’s militia.

episodes.name: Damage Assessment
episodes.overview: After a successful interrogation in Jordan, BRAVO is given devastating news that will impact the Team forever.

episodes.name: Fair Winds and Following Seas
episodes.overview: Reeling from a devastating loss, BRAVO must fight their way out of hostile territory.

episodes.name: Chaos in the Calm (1)
episodes.overview: After taking a stand against Command for better warfighter health, BRAVO is forced to the sidelines and eventually sent to Sweden on an underwhelming assignment. Lieutenant Davis is picked by Admiral Rivas to lead a new spec ops initiative.

episodes.name: Chaos in the Calm (2)
episodes.overview: BRAVO finds themselves at the scene of a terrorist attack in Sweden and Jason survives a close call. Lieutenant Davis gives her new unit an ultimatum, and a family member surprises Drew and issues a mysterious warning.

episodes.name: Ships in the Night
episodes.overview: Lieutenant Davis and Captain Walsh send BRAVO to Thailand to partner with the DEA on a joint-task force focused on the fentanyl trade. The goal is to intercept a cargo ship and acquire intel that details the Chinese government's involvement. Drew is assigned to BRAVO full-time despite his objections and a journalist later questions him about his family's history. During the mission, Drew goes rogue and makes a decision that jeopardizes everything.

episodes.name: Heroes and Criminals
episodes.overview: BRAVO targets a factory in Myanmar that the DEA has tied to China and fentanyl production. Lieutenant Davis wants the team to pull intel and destroy the plant. Jason vies for a safer plan, and some on the team begin to question his decisions.

episodes.name: A Perfect Storm
episodes.overview: Even the closest of brothers fight eventually. Tempers flare during a surveillance mission in Malaysia. As the team sets up camp in scorching hot temperatures, grievances are aired and Drew finally reveals why he's been so closed off.

episodes.name: Hundred-Year Marathon
episodes.overview: BRAVO's next mission is to capture Jun Yilin in Cambodia, but they'll be without their leaders. Ray is pulled into diplomatic negotiations and Jason travels home to help his son recover from surgery—a task that takes a dramatic turn for the worse.

episodes.name: Mission Creep
episodes.overview: BRAVO's back together and sent on a mission to verify concerning intel that links China's drug trafficking to a potential coup in Honduras. Before leaving, Jason, Ray and Drew all struggle with something personal, resulting in a volatile dynamic.

episodes.name: Appetite for Destruction
episodes.overview: BRAVO finally finds some fentanyl, officially linking Nazario to the smuggling operation. Despite instructions to keep a low-profile, Jason destroys the fentanyl and kills all the guards. Later, the team makes a shocking discovery at Nazario's camp.

episodes.name: The Sea and the Hills
episodes.overview: BRAVO returns from Nazario's camp stunned. Forced to regroup, the team hastily develops another plan to capture him, but they walk right into a trap. Later, Jason is pulled from the mission by Command and given a different objective.

episodes.name: The Last Word
episodes.overview: Does war always have the last word? Jason wrestles with guilt and searches for closure in Afghanistan. The Decker investigation comes to a close, Ray starts his new chapter and the new-look BRAVO jumps right into the next mission.
